05/09/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament opened its autumn session on Monday (4 September) by agreeing to extend the mandate of the legislature's commission for electoral reform until 15 October. Following an agreement on resuming political dialogue -- reached by the main parties last week -- the commission must now step up efforts to reconcile all legislative differences and prepare for the winter local elections.
In other news Monday, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu hailed the level of bilateral relations with Macedonia and called for more economic co-operation. His comments came during a meeting with Blagorodna Mingova Krepieva, Macedonia's new ambassador to Tirana. (Albanian News, Gazeta Sot, MRT - 05/09/06)
